<div id="outline-container-org7ab9deb" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org7ab9deb">10,000 random research questions generated by a LLM</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org7ab9deb">
<p>
This project was inspired by the LLM-generated random numbers <a href="https://sanand0.github.io/llmrandom/">work</a>, which showed that LLM's have "favorite" numbers. Here, we generate research questions and determine that at least within the field of the microbiome, Gemini 2.5 Flash Lite has favorite questions.
</p>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orga08e9cf" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="orga08e9cf"><a href="./microbiome_questions.html">Main writeup</a></h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-orga08e9cf">
<p>
This report shows you how to generate the questions, embed them, cluster them, reduce them to UMAP coordinates, and plot the results, saving it as a html.
</p>
</div>
