<div id="outline-container-org63b226d" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org63b226d"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=U35T-KzfeLk">TEDx Basel talk: my scrolling problem, and how I fixed it</a></h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org63b226d">
<p>
YouTube video of my TED talk.<br />
</p>

<p>
In this talk, I introduce the idea of the Scrolling Problem, which is the incompatiblity of my ADD brain and modern technology built around the infinite scroll. I talk about some work I'm doing to counteract that, which can be found <a href="https://github.com/tjburns08/twitter_archive_and_embed">here</a>. It was originally Twitter, but I switched to RSS mapping, <a href="https://github.com/tjburns08/rss_map">here</a>, after Twitter started blocking scrapers.
</p>
</div>
</div>
